question_in_English: In triangle ABC, a=b=c, find the magnitude of the angle A.
model_output:
Since triangle ABC is an equilateral triangle (a=b=c), all of its angles are equal. Therefore, the magnitude of angle A is the same as the magnitude of angle B and angle C. 

The sum of the angles in a triangle is 180 degrees. So, the magnitude of each angle in an equilateral triangle is 180/3 = 60 degrees. 

So, the magnitude of angle A is $\boxed{60}$ degrees.

My confidence in this answer is $\boxed{100\%}$.
